WEBVTT

00:01.610 --> 00:04.656
♪♪

00:13.361 --> 00:14.884
[ Fence rattles ]

00:31.814 --> 00:34.686
[ Cellphone rings ]

00:34.686 --> 00:36.210
[ Ring ]

00:36.210 --> 00:38.255
[ Ring ]

00:38.255 --> 00:39.865
[ Rings, stops ]

00:39.865 --> 00:42.912
♪♪

00:56.186 --> 00:58.145
[ Gunshots ]

01:03.019 --> 01:06.066
♪♪

01:15.031 --> 01:16.902
[ Cricket chirping ]

01:16.902 --> 01:18.600
Woman: Chief, will you confirm
Calvin Jackson was unarmed

01:18.600 --> 01:20.732
when he was shot?Chief Shannon: I can't comment

01:20.732 --> 01:22.560
on an open investigation.
Channel 8.

01:22.560 --> 01:24.954
Woman: When will you identify
the officer involved?

01:24.954 --> 01:26.477
It's departmental policy

01:26.477 --> 01:28.088
not to release the name
of the officer

01:28.088 --> 01:29.959
until we've completed
the investigation.

01:29.959 --> 01:32.179
We're asking the citizens
of San Francisco

01:32.179 --> 01:35.051
to please wait for the facts.

01:35.051 --> 01:36.835
Jumping
to premature conclusions

01:36.835 --> 01:40.404
doesn't help anyone,
including Mr. Jackson's family.

01:40.404 --> 01:42.232
Woman: Meanwhile tonight,
a candlelight vigil

01:42.232 --> 01:43.799
is being held
for Calvin Jackson

01:43.799 --> 01:47.498
at the Mission Terrace
Community Church.

01:47.498 --> 01:50.588
♪♪

01:59.989 --> 02:01.643
We need to talk, Mel.

02:01.643 --> 02:04.820
What, I don't call you back
so you stalk me? Good plan.

02:04.820 --> 02:06.822
Well, it would've been easier
if you'd had the courtesy

02:06.822 --> 02:08.302
to return any one
of my 14 phone calls.

02:08.302 --> 02:09.694
But hey, who's counting?

02:09.694 --> 02:11.392
Have you ever had
a private conversation

02:11.392 --> 02:13.002
with the defendant
youwere prosecuting?

02:13.002 --> 02:14.438
God, this is so wrong.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.701
I'm more than a defendant,
right?

02:16.701 --> 02:19.617
No -- You're not.

02:19.617 --> 02:22.142
You know, there are cleaner ways
to end a relationship

02:22.142 --> 02:24.448
than with a felony charge.
I-I don't deserve this.

02:24.448 --> 02:26.624
You should've
let your wife drive.

02:26.624 --> 02:28.060
She was sober.So was I, Mel.

02:28.060 --> 02:29.714
Yeah, I am not gonna argue
the case with you

02:29.714 --> 02:31.107
out here on a running trail.

02:31.107 --> 02:32.761
Then why did you accept
the assignment

02:32.761 --> 02:34.676
if you weren't gonna
offer me consideration?

02:36.025 --> 02:37.940
[ Scoffs ]

02:37.940 --> 02:40.072
You're a big name case.

02:40.072 --> 02:41.552
Raises my profile.

02:46.688 --> 02:48.951
Well, you could at least
drop the DUI,

02:48.951 --> 02:51.780
and we could both
walk away whole.

02:51.780 --> 02:53.477
This is an inappropriate
conversation

02:53.477 --> 02:56.045
on every possible level.

02:56.045 --> 02:58.221
Stop calling me.

02:58.221 --> 03:00.180
Crowd: From blue on black!Man: We're black and blue.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.878
From blue on black!We're black and blue.

03:02.878 --> 03:04.401
From blue on black!We're black and blue.

03:04.401 --> 03:06.316
From blue on black!We're black and blue.

03:06.316 --> 03:08.666
From blue on black!We're black and blue.

03:08.666 --> 03:10.538
Terry: Then I shouted
for him to stop.

03:10.538 --> 03:12.496
By the time I had made it
over the fence,

03:12.496 --> 03:14.759
the suspect was already
halfway around the corner.

03:14.759 --> 03:16.805
Subject, not the suspect.

03:16.805 --> 03:18.372
Well, he was a suspect
at the time.

03:18.372 --> 03:20.722
Oh, at the end of the alley,
there was a dead end.

03:20.722 --> 03:24.160
When the... subjectrealized
he was trapped,

03:24.160 --> 03:25.901
he turned to face me,

03:25.901 --> 03:28.730
at which point, his right arm
reached for his lower back,

03:28.730 --> 03:30.471
where I had already seen
the firearm

03:30.471 --> 03:31.863
tucked in his waistband.

03:31.863 --> 03:34.039
That was before he jumped
out the window.

03:34.039 --> 03:36.651
The same as he's told you
two times before.

03:36.651 --> 03:39.262
What kind of gun
you think you saw?

03:39.262 --> 03:40.959
You don't need to commit
to a make or a model.It was a short clip,
semi-automatic.

03:40.959 --> 03:44.224
Is it possible that what you saw
was a cellphone, not a gun?

03:44.224 --> 03:46.138
You wouldn't be the first
officer to make that mistake.

03:46.138 --> 03:47.923
No, it's not possible.

03:47.923 --> 03:50.099
I know the difference between
a cellphone and a semi.

03:50.099 --> 03:51.622
Of course you do, Inspector.

03:51.622 --> 03:53.276
You'll remain
on administrative leave

03:53.276 --> 03:55.539
pending findings
of this investigation.

03:55.539 --> 03:58.977
Uh, any idea how long
that will take?

03:58.977 --> 04:01.110
As long as necessary.

04:01.110 --> 04:03.460
With the exception of your
mandatory counseling session,

04:03.460 --> 04:05.723
you're instructed not to discuss
this case with anyone

04:05.723 --> 04:08.683
inside or outside
the department.

04:08.683 --> 04:11.163
Do you have any questions?No, ma'am.

04:11.163 --> 04:13.078
♪♪

04:13.078 --> 04:16.778
Well, actually, uh, I was on
the other side of the building.

04:16.778 --> 04:19.520
I didn't see the suspect
prior to the shooting.

04:19.520 --> 04:22.392
Um, truth be told,
Inspector Navarro and I

04:22.392 --> 04:24.829
were not in the apartment
at the time,

04:24.829 --> 04:27.484
so I-I can't
personally corroborate

04:27.484 --> 04:30.748
Inspector English's story.Thank you, Inspector.

04:30.748 --> 04:32.141
So...

04:32.141 --> 04:33.621
can you...

04:33.621 --> 04:37.929
tell us exactly what
you were doing?

04:37.929 --> 04:40.541
I was controlling three adult
females in the living room

04:40.541 --> 04:42.325
when I heard Inspector English
in the bedroom

04:42.325 --> 04:44.153
ordering the suspect
to stop.

04:44.153 --> 04:46.634
When I entered the bedroom,
he was jumping out the window.

04:46.634 --> 04:48.331
When he did so,
I saw the firearm.

04:49.637 --> 04:53.684
You...personally saw Mr. Jackson
with the weapon?

04:53.684 --> 04:56.470
I did. It was tucked into
the back of his jeans,

04:56.470 --> 04:58.950
It was the middle
to the right-hand side.

04:58.950 --> 05:01.039
How certain are you?

05:02.563 --> 05:05.261
100%.

05:05.261 --> 05:07.437
Or I wouldn't have said it.

05:14.575 --> 05:17.578
♪♪

05:21.973 --> 05:23.932
Hey there.
Good morning, Lieutenant.

05:23.932 --> 05:25.499
[ Scoffs ]

05:25.499 --> 05:27.631
Although probably not
for you today, right?

05:27.631 --> 05:29.851
I don't have time to talk
to you right now.

05:29.851 --> 05:31.635
I heard your inspector
who shot Calvin Jackson

05:31.635 --> 05:34.856
is African-American.

05:34.856 --> 05:37.337
Who told you that?

05:37.337 --> 05:39.164
Sit in a ladies' room
long enough,

05:39.164 --> 05:41.776
you hear all kinds of shit.Really?

05:41.776 --> 05:43.255
Sorry. Locker room humor.

05:43.255 --> 05:45.432
You should stick to sports,
Serena.

05:45.432 --> 05:47.129
This issports.
It's all about Normandy.

05:47.129 --> 05:49.305
Look, I can't comment during
an ongoing investigation.

05:49.305 --> 05:51.873
Okay, how about
off the record?

05:51.873 --> 05:53.831
Like I'd trust you.

05:53.831 --> 05:56.051
We both want the same thing,
okay? We both want the truth.

05:56.051 --> 05:58.009
[ Scoffs ] See,
now that's already a lie.

05:58.009 --> 06:00.316
You want a story.

06:00.316 --> 06:01.970
Truth doesn't matter
as long as it gets you

06:01.970 --> 06:03.972
more clicks on your blog.Yeah, "true" helps! Come on.

06:03.972 --> 06:06.409
I'll repeat, no comment.

06:06.409 --> 06:08.890
Which is always
a confirmation.

06:08.890 --> 06:11.240
[ Crowd shouting indistinctly ]

06:11.240 --> 06:13.721
All: We want justice!
Black lives matter!

06:13.721 --> 06:16.506
We want justice!
Black lives matter!

06:16.506 --> 06:19.291
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:19.291 --> 06:20.771
Crowd keeps gettin' bigger.

06:20.771 --> 06:22.294
Yep.

06:22.294 --> 06:24.384
Hey, did Terry talk to you
after his interview?

06:24.384 --> 06:27.125
Nope. He's following the regs.
No discussion.

06:27.125 --> 06:29.389
Really? Even with you?

06:29.389 --> 06:31.826
Navarro: Heads up.

06:31.826 --> 06:33.697
All right, what's going on
with Billy James?

06:33.697 --> 06:37.222
Well, we may have a visual ID
from a waitress at the club.

06:37.222 --> 06:38.876
She's on her way over now.

06:38.876 --> 06:41.096
She said she saw the shooter's
face as he ran out.

06:41.096 --> 06:42.967
We've set up a solid photo
array to show her.

06:42.967 --> 06:45.666
Okay.
Where are you at, Hildy?

06:45.666 --> 06:47.015
I'm working
the conspiracy angle,

06:47.015 --> 06:48.756
Looking into Normandy's
background.

06:48.756 --> 06:51.454
I'm gonna talk to his business
manager, Nick Rosenthal.

06:51.454 --> 06:53.456
And his business partner,
Sam Rydell.

06:53.456 --> 06:55.850
You think you might be spinning
your wheels with this Sam guy?

06:55.850 --> 06:57.721
Well, he wasn't at the party
according to the guest list.

06:57.721 --> 06:59.288
So it's kind of convenient.

06:59.288 --> 07:01.638
Kind of a bad week all the way
around for Sam Rydell.

07:01.638 --> 07:03.248
A celebrity spokesman
gets killed,

07:03.248 --> 07:05.468
and then his company stock
takes a 10 point dive.

07:05.468 --> 07:07.296
We're supposed to meet with him
at his place in Marin at 2:30.

07:07.296 --> 07:09.254
So... [ inhales deeply ]

07:09.254 --> 07:13.345
Well, actually,
not "we" anymore. Me.

07:13.345 --> 07:15.086
All right, Molk,
you go with Hildy.

07:15.086 --> 07:17.828
Navarro can handle
the photo ID. All right?

07:17.828 --> 07:19.308
Got it.

07:19.308 --> 07:21.005
Sam's Mondo Meat Sub
is the best.

07:21.005 --> 07:23.312
Spicy pepperoni,
succulent smoked ham,

07:23.312 --> 07:25.445
savory roast beef,
and don't forget,

07:25.445 --> 07:27.011
Sam's special sauce.

07:27.011 --> 07:29.318
[ Laughs ]
For a limited time only,

07:29.318 --> 07:31.494
you can get
a 13-inch sourdough combo

07:31.494 --> 07:34.149
for only $4.99.

07:34.149 --> 07:36.978
'Cause remember,
every inch counts.

07:36.978 --> 07:38.545
[ Chuckles ]
You can say that again.

07:38.545 --> 07:40.460
Every inch counts.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.157
Hey, go out
for a pass, Sam.

07:42.157 --> 07:43.637
Oh, yeah. Hey, go deep!

07:43.637 --> 07:46.640
♪♪

07:47.902 --> 07:49.991
Man: Sam's!

07:49.991 --> 07:52.646
Every inch counts.

07:52.646 --> 07:54.517
I remember that from the NFC
championship game last year.

07:54.517 --> 07:57.172
Yeah! Oh, damn.

07:57.172 --> 07:59.304
Me and Norm,
we had such a good time.

07:59.304 --> 08:00.958
We were more than just
best friends.

08:00.958 --> 08:03.047
He was like -- he was like
the kid brother I never had.

08:03.047 --> 08:05.049
So why weren't you
at his birthday party then?

08:05.049 --> 08:06.790
Uh, well, I sent him
a bottle of fizz.

08:06.790 --> 08:08.923
Norm, he knew I didn't approve
of the people

08:08.923 --> 08:10.315
he was hanging around.

08:10.315 --> 08:11.882
He wasn't a very good judge
of character.

08:11.882 --> 08:13.318
You know what I mean?Mm.

08:13.318 --> 08:14.842
Sorry to interrupt.Oh, hey.

08:16.583 --> 08:18.193
Oh. Um, just --

08:18.193 --> 08:20.935
just tell him I'll, uh,
I'll call him tomorrow.

08:22.632 --> 08:24.634
This is Amanda.

08:24.634 --> 08:26.854
Can I get you inspectors
anything?

08:26.854 --> 08:28.377
Coffee, water, sandwich?

08:28.377 --> 08:30.379
[ Chuckles ] No. We're good.Nothing for me.

08:30.379 --> 08:32.381
Let me know if
you change your minds.

08:34.035 --> 08:36.864
So why weren't you
into Normandy's friends?

08:36.864 --> 08:38.343
Because they weren't friends.

08:38.343 --> 08:40.215
They're just a bunch
of dog fleas.

08:40.215 --> 08:41.869
Hangers-on, users,
all of 'em.

08:41.869 --> 08:43.958
Even Billy?Especially Billy.

08:43.958 --> 08:45.263
Norm helped that kid out
six ways from Sunday

08:45.263 --> 08:47.048
their whole lives,

08:47.048 --> 08:49.137
until he finally toughened up
and canned the kid's ass,

08:49.137 --> 08:51.008
which I'd been telling him
had to happen for years.

08:51.008 --> 08:52.836
A drowning man will just
pull you right under.

08:52.836 --> 08:54.708
Well, he fired him
four weeks ago.

08:54.708 --> 08:56.753
That's a long time
to wait for payback.

08:56.753 --> 08:58.233
If Billy did it.

08:58.233 --> 08:59.669
Do you got someone else
on your list, Sam?

08:59.669 --> 09:01.062
No. Just -- I...

09:01.062 --> 09:02.759
I just can't see Billy
as a killer.

09:02.759 --> 09:05.066
But maybe I don't want to.

09:05.066 --> 09:09.418
Then I'd have to wonder
if I was partly at fault.

09:09.418 --> 09:10.854
Did I set this in motion?

09:12.726 --> 09:13.988
[ Elevator bell dings ]

09:13.988 --> 09:15.685
Oh, there he is.

09:15.685 --> 09:17.818
Alan. How are you?

09:17.818 --> 09:20.255
Mario. What a surprise.

09:20.255 --> 09:23.171
How you holding up?I'm doing well, considering.

09:23.171 --> 09:24.868
Good. That's good to hear.

09:24.868 --> 09:26.304
I'd like to ask for a minute
of your time if we could --

09:26.304 --> 09:27.741
I-I only have just a minute.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.917
I'm due back in Sacramento
this afternoon.

09:29.917 --> 09:31.527
Perfect.

09:38.795 --> 09:41.319
It's a lousy case, Alan.

09:41.319 --> 09:43.495
I know all the details,
Mario.

09:43.495 --> 09:46.237
Then why is your State Attorney
coming on like a hurricane?

09:46.237 --> 09:47.761
What is she trying to prove?

09:47.761 --> 09:50.546
How about that power doesn't
change the process?

09:50.546 --> 09:52.243
You're a defendant
like anyone else.

09:52.243 --> 09:54.332
Equal before the law.Oh, bullshit.

09:54.332 --> 09:55.943
If that were true
and there weren't

09:55.943 --> 09:57.814
any political advantages
to hammering me,

09:57.814 --> 10:00.208
this would be a negotiated plea
about a tragic accident.

10:00.208 --> 10:03.254
Wait. You came here
to negotiate with me?

10:03.254 --> 10:05.300
No, to ask
for equal treatment.

10:05.300 --> 10:08.172
A misdemeanor,
not -- not a felony.

10:08.172 --> 10:09.826
No DUI.

10:09.826 --> 10:13.221
Alan, my entire life
is on the line here.

10:13.221 --> 10:15.789
You know that. Yourlife?

10:15.789 --> 10:17.878
You killed a woman.
What about her life?

10:17.878 --> 10:20.315
The victim deserves
to have you prosecuted

10:20.315 --> 10:22.317
to the full extent
of the law, Mario.

10:22.317 --> 10:24.406
DUI, felony
vehicular manslaughter.

10:24.406 --> 10:26.800
I'm sorry.

10:26.800 --> 10:29.585
No, you're not.

10:29.585 --> 10:31.152
You love this.

10:31.152 --> 10:34.242
You still think
I wanted your job.

10:34.242 --> 10:37.593
If I'd wanted it?

10:37.593 --> 10:39.029
I'd have it.

10:46.471 --> 10:47.951
Enter.

10:51.607 --> 10:53.522
Why was Siletti here?

10:53.522 --> 10:55.219
Trying to go around you.

10:55.219 --> 10:57.744
Hoping I'd give him
some special consideration.

10:57.744 --> 10:59.920
What did you tell him?

10:59.920 --> 11:03.880
The truth. He's a sack of shit
and deserves the maximum.

11:03.880 --> 11:06.666
That's why I assigned
my most aggressive attorney.

11:08.450 --> 11:11.192
Okay, then.

11:11.192 --> 11:13.150
No mercy.

11:19.853 --> 11:22.203
The guy body-checked me
and shoved me out of the way.

11:22.203 --> 11:24.509
Everybody was freaking out,
trying to get down or run

11:24.509 --> 11:26.424
or hide, like he was gonna
keep shooting.

11:26.424 --> 11:27.861
Hmm. Luckily, he didn't.

11:27.861 --> 11:29.689
Now everything taking place
right here is being

11:29.689 --> 11:33.214
audio and videotaped,
so it's on the record.

11:33.214 --> 11:35.303
Shelly, I'm gonna show you
photos of six different men

11:35.303 --> 11:37.958
that match the description
you gave us.[ Chuckles ]

11:37.958 --> 11:39.699
I'll hand you the folders
one at a time.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.875
And you let me know your
decision about each photo

11:41.875 --> 11:43.528
before I show you
the next one, okay?

11:43.528 --> 11:45.661
Okay.
Here we go.

11:50.405 --> 11:51.885
No.
Okay. Quick.

11:51.885 --> 11:53.843
[ Chuckles ]

12:01.111 --> 12:04.419
It was so dark in there,
and his hood was up.

12:04.419 --> 12:08.684
For folder number two
is that a yes or a no, Shelly?

12:08.684 --> 12:10.947
I guess no.

12:10.947 --> 12:13.080
No. That's okay.
[ Chuckles ]

12:13.080 --> 12:14.472
[ Clears throat ]

12:25.875 --> 12:28.312
Take your time.

12:28.312 --> 12:30.097
♪♪

12:30.097 --> 12:31.533
[ Whispers ] Sorry.

12:31.533 --> 12:34.144
[ Clears throat ] Mm-hmm.

12:35.972 --> 12:38.845
No, no, I agree with --
hang on one second.

12:38.845 --> 12:40.368
Hi. Nick Rosenthal.

12:40.368 --> 12:41.848
Hi. Inspector Mulligan.Inspector Molk.

12:41.848 --> 12:43.893
[ Whispers ] Come on in.
Have a seat, sit down.

12:43.893 --> 12:46.243
Yeah. Hey, look. I gotta go.
Call you back.[ Door closes ]

12:46.243 --> 12:48.376
[ Bluetooth thuds ]I still can't believe
this happened.

12:48.376 --> 12:51.335
Keeps me up nights,
you know,

12:51.335 --> 12:54.599
thinking how Norm's dead
and Billy James is still --

12:54.599 --> 12:56.471
still out there somewhere.

12:56.471 --> 12:58.299
You were at the club the night
Normandy was killed?

12:58.299 --> 12:59.953
Yeah, but I didn't see it,
though.

12:59.953 --> 13:02.477
I was, uh...
in -- in the men's room.

13:02.477 --> 13:06.176
I, uh, I heard Alicia start
singing and then the gunshots.

13:06.176 --> 13:09.658
I just, uh, I-I froze
and stayed where I was.

13:09.658 --> 13:12.487
Do you personally know
Billy James?
Sure.

13:12.487 --> 13:13.880
Did you see him that night
at the club?

13:13.880 --> 13:15.359
I-I had no idea
he was there.

13:15.359 --> 13:17.274
I thought Normandy had
cut him off,

13:17.274 --> 13:20.669
which should've happened a lot
earlier, in my opinion.

13:20.669 --> 13:22.802
Did you advise him
to fire Billy?

13:22.802 --> 13:25.413
[ Chuckles ]
So many times.

13:25.413 --> 13:27.023
Why is that?

13:27.023 --> 13:29.504
Billy was a dead beat.

13:29.504 --> 13:31.201
All he had going for him
was the fact

13:31.201 --> 13:32.855
that they grew up together.

13:32.855 --> 13:34.988
Normandy had trouble
with "no."

13:34.988 --> 13:36.511
He let himself get taken.

13:36.511 --> 13:39.122
Believe me, I know.
I signed all the checks.

13:39.122 --> 13:41.559
Normandy was generous
to a fault.

13:41.559 --> 13:45.346
That's why his finances
are such a mess.

13:45.346 --> 13:47.783
Wait. His entire contract was
worth over $100 million.

13:47.783 --> 13:49.959
I mean, how bad could things
have been?

13:49.959 --> 13:51.961
[ Scoffs ]
$100 million over 7 years

13:51.961 --> 13:54.703
comes out to an annual salary
of $14 million.

13:54.703 --> 13:56.879
50% off the top
goes to Uncle Sam,

13:56.879 --> 13:59.882
10% to his agents,
plus my fees.

13:59.882 --> 14:01.449
You know, $100K a month
to the publicist.

14:01.449 --> 14:04.060
$200K to make sure
the hangers-on are comfortable.

14:04.060 --> 14:05.583
Oh. Thank you.

14:05.583 --> 14:08.238
And, uh, you know, he had
four car leases,

14:08.238 --> 14:10.284
three mortgages,
two kids in private schools,

14:10.284 --> 14:11.720
and a partridge in a pear tree.

14:11.720 --> 14:13.330
Do you see where
I'm going with this?

14:13.330 --> 14:15.202
So you're saying that
Normandy Parker was broke.

14:15.202 --> 14:16.681
[ Sighs ]

14:16.681 --> 14:19.032
Not broke. Cash poor.

14:19.032 --> 14:23.036
90% of his wealth was tied up
in sourdough sub stock.

14:23.036 --> 14:25.386
The three of you look
pretty tight.

14:25.386 --> 14:27.257
Yeah. Sam's the one
who introduced me

14:27.257 --> 14:28.737
to Normandy in the first place.

14:28.737 --> 14:30.695
I've been Sam's business manager
since, you know,

14:30.695 --> 14:34.003
before he opened
his first sandwich shack.

14:36.092 --> 14:38.355
We're gonna need access
to Normandy's financial records

14:38.355 --> 14:39.661
as soon as possible.

14:39.661 --> 14:43.621
Whatever, whenever,
just let me know.

14:43.621 --> 14:46.233
Can you tell me, uh,
what you were thinking

14:46.233 --> 14:48.670
in the final moments
before the shooting?

14:48.670 --> 14:51.586
There was no time to think.
I was just reacting.

14:51.586 --> 14:54.937
As a cop, as a soldier,
that's what we're --

14:54.937 --> 14:58.114
we're trained to do.

14:58.114 --> 15:00.856
Your file says you were in
the first Gulf War.

15:00.856 --> 15:03.293
Correct.Did you see combat?

15:03.293 --> 15:04.816
I've seen more combat
in the Tenderloin

15:04.816 --> 15:07.863
than I ever did at Desert Storm,
so...no.

15:11.388 --> 15:14.304
Is, um...

15:14.304 --> 15:18.004
Is Calvin Jackson
the first person you've killed?

15:20.571 --> 15:23.966
I was in pursuit of an armed man
who I thought was a murderer.

15:23.966 --> 15:25.620
I acted appropriately
in that situation.

15:25.620 --> 15:28.536
Terry, I'm not here to judge
your actions in the line --

15:28.536 --> 15:30.364
Well, everybody else is.

15:32.540 --> 15:36.500
I am a killer cop.

15:36.500 --> 15:38.850
A black killer cop

15:38.850 --> 15:41.810
that killed a black boy --

15:41.810 --> 15:45.031
an unarmed black boy.

15:47.598 --> 15:50.166
They think that I'm a traitor
to my race.

15:50.166 --> 15:52.038
Focusing on the public's
perception right now

15:52.038 --> 15:53.430
is not going to help.

15:53.430 --> 15:55.867
I would recommend
you spend time

15:55.867 --> 15:58.696
with people who know
the real you.

15:58.696 --> 16:01.743
And while I know
you can't discuss

16:01.743 --> 16:04.006
the specifics of your case,

16:04.006 --> 16:07.879
you can look to family
and friends for support.

16:07.879 --> 16:10.926
I know you're a widower.

16:10.926 --> 16:13.624
Are there people in your life
you can turn to?

16:13.624 --> 16:16.497
[ Sighs deeply ]

16:18.629 --> 16:20.196
Not really.

16:28.639 --> 16:31.077
There is yet unconfirmed
reports that Calvin Jackson

16:31.077 --> 16:33.122
was killed by
a black homicide inspector.

16:33.122 --> 16:34.994
[ Knocks ] SFPD has refused to comment.

16:34.994 --> 16:37.126
If the police don't have
anything to hide,

16:37.126 --> 16:38.736
why don't they release
the name of the cop?

16:38.736 --> 16:40.086
[ Door opens ]Man: That's right.

16:40.086 --> 16:41.522
Hey.
Hey. Morning.

16:41.522 --> 16:43.524
Yes, thank you.Ooh, you look like crap.

16:43.524 --> 16:45.134
Thank you.[ Chuckles ]

16:45.134 --> 16:46.701
[ Protestors chanting ]

16:46.701 --> 16:48.485
How long have you been
watching this?

16:48.485 --> 16:50.313
Calvin Jackson's mother thinks
the department...

16:50.313 --> 16:51.662
[ Groans ] ...is stonewalling
to protect the officers.

16:51.662 --> 16:53.490
I have no faith in the police.

16:53.490 --> 16:56.145
They murdered my boy,
and now they're covering up.

16:56.145 --> 16:58.495
Black, white, doesn't matter.

16:58.495 --> 17:02.195
That officer shot
an unarmed young man

17:02.195 --> 17:03.979
trying to surrender.All right, enough TV.

17:03.979 --> 17:05.981
Hey. How many more black men
have to die like that?

17:05.981 --> 17:07.809
So what, you came all the way
across the bridge

17:07.809 --> 17:09.419
just to come over here
and monitor my --

17:09.419 --> 17:11.117
my television programming?

17:11.117 --> 17:12.944
I didn't know you were
a masochist.

17:12.944 --> 17:15.469
Well, I've already
had my head shrunk.

17:15.469 --> 17:17.819
Let me deal with this
in my own way.

17:17.819 --> 17:19.342
So when I'mdealing
with a crisis,

17:19.342 --> 17:20.865
you want to move in with me.

17:20.865 --> 17:22.519
But when you'redealing
with a crisis,

17:22.519 --> 17:25.261
you wanna just shut me out,
do it all by yourself?

17:25.261 --> 17:28.308
That's not how it works,
Terry.

17:28.308 --> 17:31.528
Talk to me, all right?

17:31.528 --> 17:32.877
[ Cup thuds ]

17:32.877 --> 17:34.444
Tell me what's going on.

17:37.969 --> 17:41.538
Well, I've been, uh...

17:41.538 --> 17:43.627
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:43.627 --> 17:48.241
I was so sure
of what I saw.

17:48.241 --> 17:49.720
I've been telling everybody,
you know,

17:49.720 --> 17:51.244
how I did the right thing.

17:51.244 --> 17:54.856
But now I don't...

17:54.856 --> 17:57.554
I don't know
if I even believe myself.

18:00.209 --> 18:01.732
[ Exhales deeply ]

18:01.732 --> 18:04.822
I told Internal Affairs
that I saw the gun, too.

18:07.564 --> 18:10.393
What?
Mm-hmm.

18:10.393 --> 18:12.526
Hildy, no.
Yeah.

18:12.526 --> 18:14.484
You should not have lied
about that.

18:14.484 --> 18:17.270
Well...

18:17.270 --> 18:19.185
You're my partner,
you know?

18:19.185 --> 18:24.277
So if you saw a gun,
it's 'cause there was a gun.

18:31.110 --> 18:34.069
I got teams in the field
working overtime, Chief.

18:34.069 --> 18:35.897
[ Scoffs ]Chief Shannon: [ Muffled ]
I want every person

18:35.897 --> 18:37.942
in your department
working on this 24/7!

18:37.942 --> 18:39.857
The Mayor is flipping out.
I need to give him something.

18:39.857 --> 18:41.555
[ Shouts indistinctly ]

18:41.555 --> 18:43.383
Yes, I'm listening. I want updates on the hour!

18:43.383 --> 18:44.949
You know I'll keep you
in the loop, sir.

18:44.949 --> 18:46.908
Yes, sir. Of course, I --

18:46.908 --> 18:48.257
Your job's on the line here![ Line clicks, dial tone ]

18:48.257 --> 18:51.217
[ Groans, sighs ]

18:51.217 --> 18:53.871
[ Receiver thuds ]Ugh!

18:53.871 --> 18:56.309
What?A mother and her son
are here to see you.

18:56.309 --> 18:58.224
Why? I-I don't have time
for that, okay?

18:58.224 --> 19:01.357
No, you -- you want to talk
to these people, Lieutenant.

19:04.534 --> 19:07.450
Woman: I always tell my kids

19:07.450 --> 19:10.845
nevertouch a gun.

19:10.845 --> 19:15.066
I-I don't even buy them
those toy water guns.

19:15.066 --> 19:17.982
Nevertouch a gun.

19:17.982 --> 19:20.333
Isn't that what I tell you
and your brother?

19:20.333 --> 19:23.249
Yes.Say that again.

19:23.249 --> 19:25.164
Yes, ma'am.

19:25.164 --> 19:28.036
And to bring it to school?

19:28.036 --> 19:30.560
This boy has no idea

19:30.560 --> 19:32.867
the world of trouble
he could've gotten into.

19:32.867 --> 19:36.653
Where'd you get the gun,
Darryl?

19:38.089 --> 19:40.004
I was just hanging
with my friends,

19:40.004 --> 19:42.355
and then I heard sirens.

19:42.355 --> 19:44.357
I was running to see
what happened,

19:44.357 --> 19:46.620
and it was just laying there
on the ground.

19:46.620 --> 19:49.100
Do you remember where
exactly?

19:49.100 --> 19:52.278
Um...in the weeds?

19:52.278 --> 19:54.932
Next to the tree.
Then I heard people coming

19:54.932 --> 19:56.630
and got scared
and ran off with it.

19:56.630 --> 19:58.501
Which tree?Not a real one.

19:58.501 --> 20:01.678
The one on the wall,
near the fence.

20:08.729 --> 20:10.731
Is that the tree, Darryl?

20:11.993 --> 20:13.908
Yeah.

20:13.908 --> 20:16.084
I found it right there.

20:16.084 --> 20:17.607
I'm sorry.

20:17.607 --> 20:19.392
Not as sorry
as you're going to be.

20:23.091 --> 20:26.442
[ Man speaks indistinctly ]

20:26.442 --> 20:28.444
Come on, sir. Please.[ Elevator bell dings ]

20:28.444 --> 20:30.707
Yeah, yeah, totally...

20:30.707 --> 20:32.709
There's a lady waiting
for anybody in Homicide.

20:32.709 --> 20:34.320
Said she knows where to find
Billy James.

20:34.320 --> 20:36.017
Why didn't you send her
upstairs?

20:36.017 --> 20:38.149
She refused to get cancer
from the metal detector.

20:38.149 --> 20:40.978
Great. I got it, Molky.
You go upstairs.

20:40.978 --> 20:42.545
She's all yours.

20:42.545 --> 20:46.332
Afternoon, ma'am.
Inspector Mulligan, Homicide.

20:46.332 --> 20:48.812
You took long enough.Sorry about the wait.

20:48.812 --> 20:50.553
I understand you have
some information for us

20:50.553 --> 20:52.076
about Billy James.
Is that right?

20:52.076 --> 20:55.166
That kind of information
don't come free, Missy.

20:55.166 --> 20:56.516
Oh, yeah?
How much are we talkin'?[ Elevator bell dings ]

20:56.516 --> 20:57.865
$100.

20:57.865 --> 20:59.780
Wow. That's a lot.

20:59.780 --> 21:01.434
Let me see. I got...

21:03.871 --> 21:05.916
$32.
Deal.

21:05.916 --> 21:09.224
All right.
What do you got for me?

21:12.836 --> 21:14.534
This guy?

21:14.534 --> 21:17.493
He'd been sleeping on my goddamn
bench in the Dogpatch.

21:17.493 --> 21:19.974
♪♪

21:19.974 --> 21:25.240
[ Dog barking in distance ]

21:25.240 --> 21:27.503
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:27.503 --> 21:30.463
[ Barking continues ]

21:32.595 --> 21:35.424
Hey. No, no, no.
It's okay. Calm down.

21:35.424 --> 21:38.384
Have you seen
this guy before?

21:38.384 --> 21:41.256
Yeah? Where is he?

21:41.256 --> 21:42.692
Hey, hey. [ Snaps fingers ]

21:42.692 --> 21:45.216
Structure north,
corner of Cove Park.

21:45.216 --> 21:46.783
Go.

21:46.783 --> 21:50.004
[ Radio static ]

21:50.004 --> 21:52.485
[ Indistinct shouting ]Hildy: Go left!

21:52.485 --> 21:55.488
[ Indistinct shouting ]

21:55.488 --> 21:56.880
Navarro: Suspect is on foot,

21:56.880 --> 21:58.317
headed south towards
22nd Street.

21:58.317 --> 22:00.710
Officers in pursuit.
requesting backup.

22:00.710 --> 22:03.713
♪♪

22:11.721 --> 22:13.332
Aah! Aah!

22:15.682 --> 22:18.032
[ Grunting ]Stay down!

22:18.032 --> 22:21.296
Stay down! Don't move!

22:21.296 --> 22:23.820
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

22:23.820 --> 22:25.300
No weapon.

22:25.300 --> 22:27.302
Get him up.

22:27.302 --> 22:29.913
Ho, ho, ho![ Tape rips ]

22:29.913 --> 22:31.959
Ah. What you doing with
your piggy bank, Billy?

22:31.959 --> 22:34.135
You should've held up
at the Ritz-Carlton, fool.

22:34.135 --> 22:36.137
Could've had room service
till we found you.

22:36.137 --> 22:37.878
You're under arrest for
the murder of Normandy Parker.

22:37.878 --> 22:39.227
Anything you say can and will
be held against you

22:39.227 --> 22:40.750
in a court of law.

22:40.750 --> 22:42.491
You have the right to consult
with an attorney

22:42.491 --> 22:44.319
and have an attorney present
during questioning.

22:50.586 --> 22:53.154
Hildy: Nobody thinks
you did this on your own.

22:54.590 --> 22:58.202
Somebody pushed you
into it, right?

22:58.202 --> 23:00.248
Navarro:
Normandy dumps his wife,

23:00.248 --> 23:02.946
the mother of his kids,

23:02.946 --> 23:04.731
for that little pop tart --

23:04.731 --> 23:07.081
practically just a kid
herself --

23:07.081 --> 23:10.040
leaving Daphne
to cry on your shoulder.

23:10.040 --> 23:12.608
She's a beautiful woman.

23:12.608 --> 23:14.001
You've known her
since high school.

23:14.001 --> 23:16.090
Things happen. I get it.

23:16.090 --> 23:20.268
Hildy: I mean,
they were separated, right?

23:20.268 --> 23:22.488
She had a right
to her own life.

23:22.488 --> 23:25.273
It's not like she was...

23:25.273 --> 23:27.275
cheating on him with you.

23:27.275 --> 23:29.886
Right?

23:29.886 --> 23:32.019
What planet are youfrom?

23:32.019 --> 23:34.978
Personally, I don't understand
why she told him.

23:34.978 --> 23:37.024
She told him 'cause she was
trying to make him jealous.

23:37.024 --> 23:39.461
I mean,
she was fully using you.

23:39.461 --> 23:41.245
Obviously,
you know that, right?

23:41.245 --> 23:44.118
Normandy decides to blame you
instead of her

23:44.118 --> 23:46.425
and shitcans you for it.

23:46.425 --> 23:49.210
That'd piss me off to the max.

23:49.210 --> 23:51.255
Ain't that right, Hildy?

23:51.255 --> 23:53.780
Somebody noticed, right?

23:53.780 --> 23:58.654
Somebody came to you,
made you an offer.

23:58.654 --> 24:01.875
Maybe even blackmailed you.

24:01.875 --> 24:04.921
That makes more sense.

24:04.921 --> 24:07.228
You had no choice, right?

24:07.228 --> 24:09.317
Just so you know,
an admission of guilt,

24:09.317 --> 24:11.841
that actually means a lot
to the D.A.'s office.

24:11.841 --> 24:14.583
So you should probably help
yourself here

24:14.583 --> 24:16.803
and just tells us
who hired you.

24:16.803 --> 24:19.370
Otherwise, you'll be taking
the whole fall.

24:24.854 --> 24:27.291
I want a lawyer.

24:30.294 --> 24:32.166
Reardon: Yeah, I think so.

24:32.166 --> 24:33.646
Yeah, well, if you have it,
send it over.

24:33.646 --> 24:34.995
I'd really like to see it.[ Door squeaks ]

24:34.995 --> 24:36.997
That'd be great.

24:36.997 --> 24:38.389
Hey, you know what? Let me, uh,
let me call you right back.

24:38.389 --> 24:40.696
Okay? All right, thanks.
Bye.

24:40.696 --> 24:42.350
Mario. What are you doing here?

24:42.350 --> 24:45.266
Had to stop by, check in,
see how you're managing.

24:45.266 --> 24:47.790
It's all good.
It's all good, thanks.[ Door closes ]

24:47.790 --> 24:49.313
I also wanted to give you
a heads up

24:49.313 --> 24:51.054
the State may put your name
on the witness list.

24:51.054 --> 24:53.187
You and everybody else
at my party.

24:53.187 --> 24:55.972
That's the move, right?
Find my enemies.

24:55.972 --> 24:57.713
[ Chuckles ]
Well... [ clears throat ]

24:57.713 --> 24:59.672
Nobody in this office is gonna
perjure themselves to hurt you,

24:59.672 --> 25:01.325
so don't get paranoid.

25:01.325 --> 25:03.806
Oh, so you'd testify then
that I wasn't inebriated

25:03.806 --> 25:05.155
the night of the accident?

25:05.155 --> 25:08.550
I mean, you saw that
I wasn't impaired.

25:08.550 --> 25:12.815
Well, your B.A.C. report
came in under the limit.

25:12.815 --> 25:14.991
Well, not enough to convince
the State Attorney.

25:14.991 --> 25:16.645
She kept the DUI
on the table.

25:16.645 --> 25:18.429
'Cause she's trying
to make a name for herself.

25:18.429 --> 25:20.997
Ambition beats justice.

25:20.997 --> 25:22.999
But you already know that,
don't you, Marty?

25:22.999 --> 25:25.567
Look, whatever it is
you're trying to imply, I --

25:25.567 --> 25:27.003
You know, when I hired you,

25:27.003 --> 25:31.268
I saw an attorney who knew
how to win.

25:31.268 --> 25:33.444
For the right reasons.Exactly.

25:33.444 --> 25:34.794
That's what
I'm talking about.

25:34.794 --> 25:36.622
The rightreasons.

25:41.540 --> 25:45.979
If I'm called, I am duty-bound
to testify truthfully.

25:48.721 --> 25:52.246
I read a headline
this morning.

25:52.246 --> 25:54.727
"New Day for San Fran D.A.

25:54.727 --> 25:57.947
"'I intend to restore
the public's trust

25:57.947 --> 25:59.558
"in the Hall of Justice,'

25:59.558 --> 26:02.256
"said acting District Attorney,
Martin Reardon.

26:02.256 --> 26:05.128
'No one is above
the rule of the law."

26:05.128 --> 26:06.565
[ Chuckles ]

26:07.827 --> 26:10.351
You meant me, didn't you?

26:14.790 --> 26:17.184
Go home, Mario,

26:17.184 --> 26:19.316
or go somewhere else.

26:20.970 --> 26:22.842
Well...

26:22.842 --> 26:25.932
Nice to see you, Marty.

26:25.932 --> 26:28.325
You look good at my desk.

26:31.894 --> 26:34.157
[ Horn honks ]

26:34.157 --> 26:36.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:36.420 --> 26:38.248
Hey, man.
Hey.

26:40.337 --> 26:43.819
I took the liberty of ordering
for both of us.

26:43.819 --> 26:45.342
Cheers.Cheers.

26:45.342 --> 26:48.041
[ Bottles clink ]Uh... [ Clears throat ]

26:48.041 --> 26:51.566
So what, you brought me here
to work on my morale or...

26:51.566 --> 26:55.614
[ Clears throat ]
No, uh, actually, I...

26:55.614 --> 26:57.833
I wanted to see your face
when I tell you

26:57.833 --> 27:01.358
we recovered
Calvin Jackson's weapon.

27:01.358 --> 27:03.796
Where?

27:03.796 --> 27:06.842
Right where he dropped it
during the chase, by this mural.

27:06.842 --> 27:08.539
A kid grabbed it up.
A 10-year-old.

27:08.539 --> 27:10.367
And they're sure that it's
the right one?

27:10.367 --> 27:12.543
Yeah. Forensics pulled Jackson's
fingerprints off the magazine.

27:12.543 --> 27:16.460
[ Both laughs ]

27:16.460 --> 27:18.941
I was losing my mind.

27:18.941 --> 27:21.030
I was losing my mind.Hey.

27:21.030 --> 27:23.642
He made the choice, not you.
All right?

27:23.642 --> 27:25.556
I'm back.

27:25.556 --> 27:27.646
I'm back!You're back.

27:27.646 --> 27:30.823
Just as soon as you requalify.Mm. Mm-hmm.

27:30.823 --> 27:34.261
And, uh, and the Chief,
he, uh, he has one request.

27:34.261 --> 27:35.871
All right, well,
if it's the Chief,

27:35.871 --> 27:39.309
then it's not a request.[ Scoffs ] Yeah, true enough.

27:39.309 --> 27:41.834
He wants us to get out in front
of the public's reaction

27:41.834 --> 27:45.489
with a news conference,
starring him and you.

27:48.579 --> 27:50.016
I don't know, man.
I don't...

27:50.016 --> 27:52.018
Hey... [ Sighs deeply ]

27:52.018 --> 27:55.151
You...you shot someone
in self-defense, all right?

27:55.151 --> 27:57.023
That's what we'll say
at the press conference

27:57.023 --> 27:59.286
'cause that's the truth.

27:59.286 --> 28:00.809
I gotta make a statement?

28:00.809 --> 28:03.246
Just a brief one.
I'll walk you through it.

28:03.246 --> 28:05.466
You set the record straight,
you start closing cases again.

28:05.466 --> 28:08.208
You okay with that?What if I wasn't?

28:08.208 --> 28:11.167
Well, like you said,
it's not a request.

28:11.167 --> 28:12.778
Not a request.
Yeah.

28:17.173 --> 28:20.176
[ Gunshots ]

28:20.176 --> 28:25.791
♪♪

28:25.791 --> 28:28.794
♪♪

28:32.362 --> 28:35.409
Man: Inspector English,
the commission unanimously

28:35.409 --> 28:38.107
finds you clear
of any misconduct.

28:38.107 --> 28:42.285
♪♪

28:42.285 --> 28:43.809
Thanks.

28:43.809 --> 28:45.419
[ Applause ]Molk: Hey, hey, hey!

28:45.419 --> 28:47.290
Terry: Hey, all right.Navarro: Yeah!

28:47.290 --> 28:49.205
Welcome home.
All right. All right.Thanks, fellas.

28:49.205 --> 28:51.773
Good to see you. Hey, man.
All right.Good to see you.

28:51.773 --> 28:53.340
Hey, you.Hey.

28:53.340 --> 28:56.430
So what, uh, did I miss
that I couldn't see on TV?

28:56.430 --> 28:58.475
Uh, Billy James --
he lawyered up.

28:58.475 --> 29:00.564
And the club waitress couldn't
pick him out of a photo array.

29:00.564 --> 29:02.610
All right, so what was put on
the voucher when you booked him?

29:02.610 --> 29:05.134
No weapon.But 4 grand in cash.

29:05.134 --> 29:06.701
So he could've left town,
but he didn't.

29:06.701 --> 29:08.616
Mm, not really enough
to start a new life,

29:08.616 --> 29:09.965
even in Mexico.Mnh-mnh.

29:09.965 --> 29:12.011
Planned a murder
minus an exit strategy.

29:12.011 --> 29:15.275
Unless he stayed and was
waiting for something.Or someone.

29:15.275 --> 29:17.320
Like maybe the rest
of the payout?From whoever hired him.

29:17.320 --> 29:20.106
Mm-hmm.That's why he never bounced.

29:23.805 --> 29:26.199
Hey, Terry.Molky.

29:26.199 --> 29:28.288
How you holding up?[ Beeping ]

29:28.288 --> 29:31.639
I am good.Good, good.

29:31.639 --> 29:33.249
You know, listen,

29:33.249 --> 29:34.990
there's something I wanted
to say privately to you

29:34.990 --> 29:38.167
is just that I'm just really
sorry that you had to go through

29:38.167 --> 29:40.953
all that drama publicly.

29:43.564 --> 29:46.262
Thanks, Molk. Appreciate that.

29:46.262 --> 29:47.829
I mean, you know, as far
as I'm concerned,

29:47.829 --> 29:49.875
there's -- there's just --
there's no such thing as --

29:49.875 --> 29:52.399
as -- as white cops
or -- or black cops

29:52.399 --> 29:54.793
or -- or female cops,
and that we're all --

29:54.793 --> 29:57.447
we're all just cops,
you know?

29:59.275 --> 30:00.929
Well --Anyway, I-I just --

30:00.929 --> 30:02.844
I-I know it must've been
really hard

30:02.844 --> 30:04.541
for you to go through,
and I --

30:04.541 --> 30:07.936
I'm just really glad
it's all over.

30:07.936 --> 30:10.417
Okay.

30:10.417 --> 30:11.853
Okay, I appreciate that.

30:11.853 --> 30:13.681
[ Chuckles ]

30:13.681 --> 30:15.335
Thanks, Molk.
Yeah.

30:15.335 --> 30:19.426
Whoop. Okay.
Yeah.

30:19.426 --> 30:22.168
Thanks, Molk.
Yeah.

30:22.168 --> 30:23.604
[ Elevator bell dings ]

30:23.604 --> 30:25.301
I get what you're saying.
I understand that.

30:25.301 --> 30:27.173
I know you wanna keep him
in custody. So do I.

30:27.173 --> 30:28.609
But simply put, there isn't
enough evidence

30:28.609 --> 30:30.176
for me to charge him with murder
at this point.

30:30.176 --> 30:33.266
Okay, we just need a little more
time to lay track.

30:33.266 --> 30:34.571
[ Sighs heavily ]

30:34.571 --> 30:36.573
You got no usable
security tapes.

30:36.573 --> 30:39.011
You got no witness ID.
You got no murder weapon.

30:39.011 --> 30:40.360
That's no case!

30:40.360 --> 30:42.057
I can't charge him
on wishful thinking.

30:42.057 --> 30:44.016
Billy James is the shooter,
Martin.

30:44.016 --> 30:45.713
Well, then you rearrest him
when you have enough

30:45.713 --> 30:47.628
actualevidence
to make the case.

30:47.628 --> 30:50.326
In the meantime,
you cut him loose.

30:50.326 --> 30:53.329
♪♪

31:01.947 --> 31:03.383
You see, Reardon's just
looking for votes.

31:03.383 --> 31:04.906
He wants to keep
this gig long-term.

31:04.906 --> 31:06.647
[ Scoffs ] Never thought
I'd miss Siletti.

31:06.647 --> 31:08.301
All right, let's get practical.

31:08.301 --> 31:09.868
We need a judge to authorize
a tap on Billy's phone

31:09.868 --> 31:11.782
and a transponder in his car.

31:11.782 --> 31:13.567
He doesn't leave his grandma's
yard without us on him. Clear?

31:13.567 --> 31:15.743
What if Billy is sticking
around town just to wait

31:15.743 --> 31:17.614
for his partner to make
this final payment?

31:17.614 --> 31:20.052
He feels safe, he's gonna slip.
He's gonna make contact.

31:20.052 --> 31:22.532
We just gotta be patient.All right.

31:22.532 --> 31:24.665
Arkin:
I can't even imagine

31:24.665 --> 31:27.755
what the hell you thought
you were doing.

31:27.755 --> 31:31.367
How is harassment supposed
to work in your favor? Huh?

31:31.367 --> 31:34.980
I got three complaints
about you in one day.

31:34.980 --> 31:36.372
That's a personal record.

31:36.372 --> 31:39.114
Right? Martin Reardon,
Melissa Danson,

31:39.114 --> 31:41.160
the Attorney General, himself,
for Christ sakes.

31:41.160 --> 31:42.901
Were you -- were you gonna
hit up the Governor next?

31:42.901 --> 31:44.293
If I thought it would
help our case

31:44.293 --> 31:45.686
and if I had a personal
relationship --

31:45.686 --> 31:47.470
I-I told you already.

31:47.470 --> 31:49.211
The only personal relationship
that matters is with your wife.

31:49.211 --> 31:50.952
I didn't engage you
for marital advice, Al.

31:50.952 --> 31:54.434
You know, your mouthis
your number one problem.

31:54.434 --> 31:57.176
But your wifeis number two
on that list.

31:57.176 --> 31:59.091
If Cassie decides to testify
for the --

31:59.091 --> 32:00.527
She can't be compelled.

32:00.527 --> 32:03.747
But we can't stop her
if she wants to.

32:03.747 --> 32:06.098
Shedecides.

32:06.098 --> 32:09.579
So how is that gonna go
exactly?

32:09.579 --> 32:12.931
Because the rest of your life
depends on what she does,

32:12.931 --> 32:16.935
including jail time,
disbarment,

32:16.935 --> 32:19.111
permanent status as a felony,

32:19.111 --> 32:22.070
and all of the consequences
that go with that.

32:22.070 --> 32:24.420
Hell, you -- you couldn't even
visit Canada.

32:26.379 --> 32:29.382
Are you married, Al?Divorced.

32:29.382 --> 32:31.471
Then you don't get it.

32:34.343 --> 32:36.606
Um, one more thing.

32:36.606 --> 32:38.739
You're still behind
on your bill, Mario.

32:40.262 --> 32:41.698
I need a check by tomorrow.

32:44.571 --> 32:48.053
Protestors: [ Chanting ] We want
justice! Black lives matter!

32:48.053 --> 32:50.751
We want justice!
Black lives matter!

32:50.751 --> 32:54.668
We want justice!
Black lives matter!

32:54.668 --> 32:56.278
Inspector Terrance English
has served

32:56.278 --> 32:59.325
the San Francisco Police
Department with distinction

32:59.325 --> 33:01.414
for nearly a decade.

33:01.414 --> 33:03.633
And in that time,
he's proven himself to be

33:03.633 --> 33:06.941
of excellent character
and reputation.

33:06.941 --> 33:08.987
The Police Commission has
determined that his actions

33:08.987 --> 33:13.556
were performed in the best
interest of public safety.

33:13.556 --> 33:15.689
Therefore,

33:15.689 --> 33:21.042
he will be reinstated to duty
effective immediately.

33:21.042 --> 33:24.480
Inspector English has asked
to make a personal statement.

33:27.048 --> 33:28.876
[ Camera shutters clicking ][ Whispers ] Thank you, sir.

33:28.876 --> 33:31.357
[ Clears throat ]

33:31.357 --> 33:34.273
[ Clears throat ]

33:34.273 --> 33:36.579
[ Camera shutters
continue clicking ]

33:39.060 --> 33:41.323
[ Inhales deeply ]

33:41.323 --> 33:42.890
[ Exhales deeply ]

33:44.631 --> 33:49.549
It is our job
to protect and serve

33:49.549 --> 33:52.465
every member of our community.

33:52.465 --> 33:55.120
And I will continue to do so

33:55.120 --> 33:59.254
as long as I have the honor
of wearing my star.

34:01.039 --> 34:04.607
I offer deep condolences

34:04.607 --> 34:07.480
to Mr. Jackson's family.

34:12.789 --> 34:14.835
Uh...

34:17.316 --> 34:19.579
Thank you, Inspector --Oh, I'm not done yet.

34:19.579 --> 34:20.928
[ Whispers ] Excuse me.Sorry.

34:20.928 --> 34:25.628
[ Shutters continue clicking ]

34:31.286 --> 34:33.071
Look at me.

34:35.290 --> 34:36.770
Look at me.

34:39.294 --> 34:42.906
I'm the same color
as Calvin Jackson.

34:45.692 --> 34:48.564
This isn't about race.

34:48.564 --> 34:52.960
That day, I had every reason
to believe

34:52.960 --> 34:56.920
that I was chasing
an armed murderer.

34:58.487 --> 35:00.750
I saw the gun.

35:00.750 --> 35:04.363
I saw him reaching for his gun.

35:04.363 --> 35:07.192
Now at the time, neither one
of us knew he dropped it,

35:07.192 --> 35:10.151
but that day,

35:10.151 --> 35:13.850
Calvin Jackson
was prepared to kill me.

35:15.330 --> 35:17.550
Now the gun was recovered,

35:17.550 --> 35:21.597
and Mr. Jackson's prints
were on it,

35:21.597 --> 35:24.948
but...

35:24.948 --> 35:29.214
my question is this --

35:29.214 --> 35:33.783
would the community

35:33.783 --> 35:38.962
have put together just as many
vigils and protests

35:38.962 --> 35:41.443
for me...

35:41.443 --> 35:44.925
if Ihad been killed...

35:44.925 --> 35:47.145
in the line of duty?

35:55.457 --> 35:56.850
Now I'm done.

35:56.850 --> 35:59.983
[ Reporters shouting at once ]

35:59.983 --> 36:02.595
Thank you. There will be
no more questions.

36:02.595 --> 36:04.336
Thank you. Thank you, all.

36:04.336 --> 36:06.207
[ Reporters continue shouting
at once ]

36:06.207 --> 36:08.818
♪♪

36:08.818 --> 36:10.168
[ Bell clanging ]

36:23.355 --> 36:25.095
They don't want to see you,
Mario.

36:25.095 --> 36:27.620
I have had a miserable day and I
don't wanna fight with you.

36:27.620 --> 36:29.622
So can you just tell your sister
that I'm here?

36:29.622 --> 36:31.189
No. I won't.

36:31.189 --> 36:32.538
For years I've been saying
she should take Michael

36:32.538 --> 36:35.541
and leave your lying ass.
Let her go.

36:35.541 --> 36:37.978
Well, why don't you slam
the door in my face --

36:37.978 --> 36:41.111
[ Door alert chiming ]

36:41.111 --> 36:44.071
[ Chiming stops ]

36:49.207 --> 36:52.210
[ Pounding seat belt holster ]

36:55.430 --> 36:56.736
[ Dog barking in distance ]

36:56.736 --> 36:58.433
[ Knock on window ]

37:00.348 --> 37:01.784
[ Door opens ]

37:09.270 --> 37:12.099
You're not supposed
to be driving.

37:12.099 --> 37:13.753
That's the least
of my problems.

37:17.235 --> 37:19.802
You wanted to talk.
Here I am.

37:26.113 --> 37:29.421
I miss you.

37:29.421 --> 37:31.945
I'm asking for you and Michael
to come home.

37:31.945 --> 37:35.731
I need you, Cass.

37:35.731 --> 37:39.039
We're a family.

37:43.913 --> 37:46.960
You know, I keep seeing that
woman over and over,

37:46.960 --> 37:50.398
her body hitting
the windshield.

37:50.398 --> 37:53.140
I can't sleep.I can't either.

37:53.140 --> 37:55.229
Yeah, 'cause you're worried

37:55.229 --> 37:56.970
about what's gonna happen
to you.Because I am worried about us.

37:58.928 --> 38:01.801
Do you ever think
about her?

38:01.801 --> 38:05.500
[ Voice breaks ] Mario,
her kids, her husband.

38:05.500 --> 38:07.285
All the time.

38:09.287 --> 38:10.853
I destroyed a family
in a second.

38:10.853 --> 38:13.639
I-I -- How do I fix that?

38:15.467 --> 38:17.469
I can't.

38:17.469 --> 38:19.297
[ Whispers ] I can't.

38:21.821 --> 38:25.868
That's the first time I've ever
heard any regret from you...

38:25.868 --> 38:29.176
about anything.

38:29.176 --> 38:31.483
[ Whispers ] 20 years
we've been married.

38:34.442 --> 38:37.619
You picked yourself
a lousy partner.

38:40.883 --> 38:43.930
[ Inhales sharply ]

38:43.930 --> 38:46.802
Well, I thought
youpicked me.[ Laughs ]

38:51.024 --> 38:53.940
Yeah. It was the best decision
I ever made.

38:55.463 --> 38:59.380
'Cause you made me better
than I was.

38:59.380 --> 39:01.208
You still do.

39:02.427 --> 39:06.039
I screwed up, Cassie.

39:06.039 --> 39:09.651
I've been so selfish.

39:09.651 --> 39:12.611
I've done so many
stupid things.

39:12.611 --> 39:16.092
And I let you
get away with it.

39:16.092 --> 39:18.051
[ Sniffles ]

39:18.051 --> 39:19.966
All the women...Not so many. No.

39:19.966 --> 39:22.708
And if I hadn't been arguing
about the latest one...

39:22.708 --> 39:25.754
Don't -- don't -- Cassie don't....if I didn't grab that phone,

39:25.754 --> 39:28.931
you would've still been
watching the road.

39:28.931 --> 39:32.935
And I'd have still
been tanked.

39:32.935 --> 39:36.678
This is my fault, not yours.
Not in any way at all.

39:37.984 --> 39:39.507
Okay?

39:39.507 --> 39:43.642
So don't -- don't do this.

39:43.642 --> 39:45.687
Cassie...

39:45.687 --> 39:47.602
Hey.[ Sniffles ]

39:47.602 --> 39:50.170
Will you and Michael
come home?

39:55.480 --> 39:57.395
I don't know.

40:04.967 --> 40:06.621
[ Car door closes ]

40:14.455 --> 40:16.152
[ Knocks on door ]

40:16.152 --> 40:17.893
Hey.
Hey.

40:17.893 --> 40:19.808
I, um...

40:19.808 --> 40:22.463
I wanted to...
I wanted to see you.

40:22.463 --> 40:23.986
Yeah, come in.

40:28.730 --> 40:30.036
I saw the news.

40:30.036 --> 40:33.082
Yeah. Yeah.You spoke from your heart.

40:34.519 --> 40:37.696
Right. Uh, Chief's pissed.

40:37.696 --> 40:39.524
Well, he's not gonna be
once he sees

40:39.524 --> 40:41.264
all the positive stuff
on Twitter.

40:41.264 --> 40:43.353
I hope so.

40:45.312 --> 40:47.749
Um...No, no. Wait, wait.

40:47.749 --> 40:49.185
Hmm?Hey, Terry!

40:49.185 --> 40:52.362
Hey, missy. What's --
what's happenin'?

40:52.362 --> 40:54.713
Uh...We're having
a movie marathon.

40:54.713 --> 40:56.236
You should stay
and watch with us.

40:56.236 --> 40:58.151
Movie -- no, no, I'll just
let you two do it.

40:58.151 --> 40:59.805
-No.
-No, you can stay.
-No, I just wanted to drop by --

40:59.805 --> 41:01.328
No, no, no. You're gonna stay.
Come on.

41:01.328 --> 41:02.938
All right, this...
I'll leave you to it.

41:02.938 --> 41:04.723
No, you gotta stay.
No, we want you. You gotta stay.

41:04.723 --> 41:06.768
Are you sure?Yeah, for sure.
For sure, for sure.

41:06.768 --> 41:09.336
I mean, is there enough popcorn
in there for me or...

41:09.336 --> 41:11.643
There's more. It only takes
three minutes in a micro.

41:11.643 --> 41:14.036
-How long does it take?
-Three minutes.
-[ Hildy laughing ]

41:14.036 --> 41:15.647
How long does it take?Three minutes. [ Laughs ]

41:15.647 --> 41:17.431
In a what?In a micro.

41:17.431 --> 41:19.389
In a micro?

41:19.389 --> 41:22.044
Turn it on.All right. [ Sighs ]

41:22.044 --> 41:25.091
♪♪
